A. RIGHT TO CURE/TERMINATION FOR SUBCONTRACTOR'S DEFAULT
After several days prior communication to Subcontractor for EDGE's possible termination , EDGE may terminate this Agreement, or any one or more awarded Purchase Orders and take full control of the Work for such terminated Purchase Orders, including any or all materials for the Work, and may proceed with the completion of the Work as contemplated by this Agreement by whatever method is EDGE's preference upon the occurrence of the following events, which shall be deemed events of a default by Subcontractor hereunder:

1) Subcontractor fails to supply an adequate number of workers or standard materials or equipment for performance of the Work;

2) Subcontractor fails to make payments to its Lower-tier Subcontractors or employees or laborers for labor, material or equipment;

